description:
Psylocke has returned to the X-Men! Following the defeat of Madelyne Pryor and her Sisterhood, Psylocke travels to Japan to re-inter her former body in its proper resting place. But when a swarm of Hand ninjas attack Psylocke and do the unspeakable under orders from Matsu’o—the assassin originally responsible for transplanting Psylocke’s mind into the body of an Asian ninja— Psylocke determines that Matsu’o is one loose end that can no longer be left unresolved. It’s a tale of carnage and revenge, brought to you by superstars Chris Yost ( X-FORCE) and Harvey Tolibao ( AVENGERS: THE INITIATIVE)!

The four issues are collected in the trade paperback X-Men: Psylocke.

Translated into Spanish.
name: Psylocke

description:
Previously published as Ozzie and Babs, while marked as issues # 14 and 15 the inside of the comic indicates they were really issues 1 & 2 of TV Teens, and with # 3 the numbering was changed.

At first about the adventures of three horny teenage boys obsessed with the new media of television, and Babs the girlfriend of one of the boys, this theme soon degenerated into yet another Archie imatation, and then was replaced for one issue with the incongruously titled TV Teens presents Don Winslow of the Navy, which reprinted one issue of the adventure comic that Fawcett had published in the 40’s, after that the comic was given over to reprints of St. Johns' Modsy with new covers.
name: TV Teens
